Certainly! Below is a simple web application that creates a red ball bouncing up and down using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. You can copy and paste the following code into a single HTML file, and then open that file in a web browser to see the bouncing ball in action.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bouncing Ball</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }

        #ball {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background-color: red;
            border-radius: 50%;
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            animation: bounce 0.8s infinite alternate;
        }

        @keyframes bounce {
            from {
                transform: translateY(0);
            }
            to {
                transform: translateY(-300px);
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="ball"></div>

<script>
    const ball = document.getElementById('ball');

    // To dynamically adjust the bounce height
    let bouncing = true;

    // Function to toggle bounce state
    function toggleBounce() {
        bouncing = !bouncing;
        if (bouncing) {
            ball.style.animationPlayState = 'running';
        } else {
            ball.style.animationPlayState = 'paused';
        }
    }

    // Event listener to toggle bounce on click
    ball.addEventListener('click', toggleBounce);
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the entire code block above.
2. Paste it into a new file and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `bouncing_ball.html`).
3. Open the file in your web browser.

### Features:
- A red ball appears at the bottom of the screen and bounces up and down continuously.
- You can click on the ball to pause or resume the bouncing effect.

Feel free to modify the styles or the animation properties to create your custom bouncing experience!
